Movie: Once Upon a Time in the West

Review: Billy Elliot is one of the most tear-jerking success stories ever to be put on film. Black Swan aint got nothing on this
Got some real Pirates trilogy vibes during the first battle. I love it when someone screams FIRE and a bunch of cannons blast off. Really gets me going
It would have been much more interesting without the final act but I did enjoy the majority of the film.
GUCCI paid to restore this film, classiest thing they ever did
This could have easily been on the shelf at Blockbuster. Will be recommending to my grandparents

Movie: Indiana Jones and the Dial of Destiny
Review: People are mad because this wasn't a searing psychoanalysis on Dr. Jones's character but it doesn't need to be all that. Harison was excellent and I loved it when John Rhys-Davies showed up. It was also nice seeing Karen Allen. Can't this just be a fun film about old chaps enjoying their golden years, settling down but never losing the edge? I even liked the co-star and that kid. Plot got a little looney but the action was good. It seemed like everyone was having a really nice time.
Have you ever walked away from a Wes Anderson movie hyperaware of all the 90° turns you make?
